‚úÖ Step-by-Step: Check if xp_cmdshell is Enabled
sql
Copy
Edit
-- Allow advanced options to be shown
EXEC sp_configure 'show advanced options', 1;
RECONFIGURE;

-- Check the current status of xp_cmdshell
EXEC sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell';


üîç Output Explanation
The key columns are:

name: should be xp_cmdshell

config_value: 1 means enabled, 0 means disabled (the intended setting)

run_value: the value currently in effect

Example:
plaintext
Copy
Edit
name         | minimum | maximum | config_value | run_value
-------------|---------|---------|--------------|-----------
xp_cmdshell  | 0       | 1       | 0            | 0
In this case, xp_cmdshell is disabled.

üõ†Ô∏è Enable xp_cmdshell (if needed)
To enable it (requires sysadmin role):

sql
Copy
Edit
-- Show advanced options
EXEC sp_configure 'show advanced options', 1;
RECONFIGURE;

-- Enable xp_cmdshell
EXEC sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell', 1;
RECONFIGURE;
